Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.72,0:00:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad's birthday -
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.32,0:00:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte and dad celebrated it \Nwith a sumptuous party for just the two of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.59,0:00:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if dad nearly failed to show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.77,0:00:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thankfully, the girl knew that patience always pays off.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.19,0:00:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time, Lotte could muster the courage \Nto ask dad's permission to kiss him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.10,0:00:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if she did it as Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.97,0:00:28.98,Sign,,0,0,105,,{\c&HD2FFFF&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20\fscy105}Episode 9 \N {\fs35} Mom's Home Cooking {お母さんの手料理} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.16,0:00:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There, there, what'll you do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.73,0:00:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Still wanna defy me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.91,0:00:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Please stop, it hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.98,0:00:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.18,0:00:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, you're not getting away \Nwith harassing Ilse again!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.96,0:00:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? \NIf I'm not getting away, try to stop me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.17,0:00:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You alright, Ilse?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.34,0:00:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back here, Annie!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.54,0:00:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back I said, Annie!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.76,0:00:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back my bottoms! {/won't catch}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.60,0:01:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.47,0:01:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Got you! Told you, not getting away.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.21,0:01:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh! I was never even trying!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.03,0:01:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This will teach you not to bully Ilse ever again!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.14,0:01:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.74,0:01:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.99,0:01:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you promise me \Nnot to resort to violence again?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.83,0:01:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But mom, even together, me and you never managed \Nto figure out a way to stop her without slapping her. {unsure, maybe issho ni here refers to ilsa}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.64,0:01:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we didn't? My bad, my bad. \NWe'll definitely try again sometime. {not sure, "place of here busy"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.28,0:01:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Smells like smoke!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.36,0:01:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.93,0:01:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Only the charcoals are left. {/it's pitch back}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.62,0:01:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Annie's fault, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.12,0:01:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was cooking, when I saw her \Nbullying Ilsa in the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.67,0:01:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this sometimes happens, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.96,0:01:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,How about we eat in a restaurant today? {/outside}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.68,0:02:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? For real?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.06,0:02:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You can count on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.74,0:02:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been rewarded heftily \Nfor the recent manuscripts.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.16,0:02:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We can afford some splurging.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.47,0:02:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Splendid!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.74,0:02:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I should consider burning our meal more often! {/should I make a blunder every day?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.31,0:02:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You crafty thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.15,0:02:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, mom, did you reserve \Nboth the table and the food? {lit: did reservation of food too - I hope she means "you reserved the table, but did you also reserve the order already?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.66,0:02:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you order?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.29,0:02:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather keep that a surprise. \NBut I have no doubt you'll be pleased with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.96,0:02:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just say it's your one very favorite dish.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.20,0:02:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoah! What could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.88,0:02:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A Burgundian sole fillet, \Ngarnished with champignons. {no clue what is fuu: burugunyuu XXX kinoko, maybe "burgundian style/manner"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.05,0:02:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Your favorite, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.72,0:02:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No way... \NI can't stand eating any fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.82,0:02:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always so full of bones!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.54,0:02:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what you told me back in the day,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.45,0:02:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,"It's so delicious, I could eat \Nten plates of it at once!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.69,0:02:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh. That's how it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.88,0:03:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, it's getting cold. {/will you eat}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.48,0:03:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.97,0:03:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all things, Lotte ended up \Nbeing head over heels for fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.15,0:03:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's something I'd rather know beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.98,0:03:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, maybe I would have \Naverted it somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.48,0:03:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Was very tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.38,0:03:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Want a refill?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.01,0:03:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, I'm full already.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.74,0:03:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My, why did you make such a mess of it? {/why did you eat it in that way}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.28,0:03:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.53,0:03:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Mom's fish bones look perfectly intact! {looks like an example; specimen; sample - not sure what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.65,0:03:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You used to keep it intact, too. \NEven better than I do. {/more clean/pretty}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.89,0:03:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.54,0:03:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.64,0:03:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This change in you is beyond explainable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.80,0:03:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This, and how you suddenly \Nacquired a taste for omelette. And also...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.90,0:03:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Before, whenever I would propose going to a restaurant, \Nyou'd say, "No, it's too expensive," and stop me. {/it's a waste and would stop me}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.37,0:03:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured, if it's mom's idea, it should be good, \Nso I must comply with it, without objections.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.55,0:04:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. Well, if that's the case, \NI can but to encourage it. {/welcome}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! This woman is pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.92,0:04:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She looks familiar. \NIsn't she a famous model?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.31,0:04:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I see her a lot in fashion magazines!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.60,0:04:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed a colleague here. {/acquintance}\NMind if I come pay my respects?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.40,0:04:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.40,0:04:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.00,0:04:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.09,0:04:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein Lotte, it's been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.54,0:04:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.18,0:04:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Whew, this is dangerous. \NSeems like he knows me. Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.42,0:04:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That Frau in Helen, you know her?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.73,0:04:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, name rings a bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.76,0:04:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm considering using her photo \Nfor our next gravure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.89,0:04:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We came here to fix the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.00,0:04:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Gravure?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.94,0:04:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.29,0:04:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Editor-in-Chief Bernau!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.93,0:04:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's me. \NDid you just now remembered it, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.83,0:04:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's been half a year, \Nbut am I really that forgettable a guy? {in the background; not standing out​}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.75,0:04:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.04,0:04:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember you very well. {/know other things too}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.26,0:04:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a devoted bachelor, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.78,0:05:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Proudly so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.82,0:05:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, you're also a thorn in mom's side. {I don't seem to find anyone using it like that, but should be "friends that quarrel a lot" but with a slightly offensive tint}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.45,0:05:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.22,0:05:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,My, Lotte! Mind your tongue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.49,0:05:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's honestly a revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.47,0:05:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, you have changed a good deal \Nsince our last meeting, I can swear. {/lately}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.69,0:05:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.34,0:05:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, and even people from outside our family \Nare all saying Lotte had changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.23,0:05:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If I keep giving them that kind of impression, \NI'll be in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.12,0:05:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Worst case scenario - everyone finds out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.65,0:05:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.75,0:05:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You {\i1}what?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.45,0:05:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Want me to teach you to cook meat?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.49,0:05:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh. If only you have some free time for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.39,0:05:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I have the time for it... {/you're saying in my free time - no clue what he imples}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.32,0:05:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr, you know how to cook, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.95,0:05:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.96,0:05:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't I the one who taught you \Nmost of the recipes you know to-date?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.17,0:05:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, this... This is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.01,0:05:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No further questions, then. It's decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.84,0:06:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind it, but most of the meat dishes I know \Nyou should already know how to cook yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.22,0:06:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, as of late, a great many things had happened, \Nand my cooking expertise may had been blunted. {I was busy with studying}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.54,0:06:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I heard you. \NI'll take you in as a disciple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.17,0:06:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.80,0:06:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everything I taught you before \Nno longer good enough for you? {/I havenothing more to teach you over ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.06,0:06:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I just forgot a lot of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.90,0:06:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You forgot?! Oh, come on! Next, you'll tell me \Nyou're not actually Lotte! {most likely katsugu - "to take (someone) for a ride; to deceive; to take in"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.84,0:06:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have truly forgotten!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.85,0:06:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you do it for me, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.66,0:06:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, so be it. How can you say no, \Nwhen Lotte is asking so earnestly? {not really sure what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.01,0:06:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.61,0:06:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it you called me out for?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.65,0:06:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.52,0:06:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out, she's about to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.42,0:06:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Not before you defeat us first!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.59,0:06:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I'm not here to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.56,0:06:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize for what I did before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.87,0:07:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When the steak looks brown enough, \Npromptly flip it over. {burn mark; grilled surface (e.g. on a steak)}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.74,0:07:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you try yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.31,0:07:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.41,0:07:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, you okay, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.62,0:07:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,More or less. {/I'll manage}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.55,0:07:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now it's time to peel the onions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.18,0:07:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,First you cut out the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.49,0:07:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.54,0:07:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, try it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.04,0:07:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's easy if you don't rush yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.92,0:07:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Haste makes waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.88,0:07:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.14,0:07:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.41,0:07:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.37,0:07:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like nothing serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.91,0:07:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's the fifth time today!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.66,0:07:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If you keep this up, \Nyou'll be left with no fingers soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.34,0:07:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it can't be that bad, Frau. {exaggerated; overdone; overblown; hyperbolic; bombastic; grandiose}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.99,0:07:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.53,0:07:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.94,0:07:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you say so, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.81,0:08:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A small blister is still there, \Nbut it doesn't hurt anymore. It'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.87,0:08:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one could use one more bandage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.54,0:08:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! Tonight, I'm not making any blunders,\Nwhile cooking a delicious meal!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.83,0:08:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Mhm! Today's vegetables soup melts in my mouth! \NAnd the meat is also just the right degree of tenderness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.14,0:08:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.34,0:08:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How can it not be perfect, \Nafter all those hardships?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.83,0:08:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What happened to that finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.18,0:08:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Just squeezed it a bit with the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.04,0:09:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,My, how most unusual to see Lotte getting hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.02,0:09:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.08,0:09:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.83,0:09:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring to the common denominator...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.89,0:09:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Still not in the bed, Lotte? \NYou should stop now, it's time to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.98,0:09:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.24,0:09:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The real Lotte, by now, \Nis probably fast asleep already.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.19,0:09:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But here, a certain Fraulein Luise has to work more and more, \Nin order to make a convincing Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.16,0:09:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day, cooking is my main concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.01,0:09:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if I pretend being Lotte, her level of cooking \Nand her perfect scores on the test are still out of my reach. {lit: so that lotte doesn't find out - not sure what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.87,0:10:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! You'll get us discovered! {/she did it}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.73,0:10:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why, sometimes, I can't help wondering \Nwhat would it have been like, if I just stayed Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.16,0:10:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But because I'm going through this with my dear mom, \NI can bear a bit of hardships for the sake of staying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.78,0:10:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good question. If I had still been living as Lotte, \Nwhere would I have been by now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.01,0:10:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.54,0:10:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It looked like she was too engrossed in some letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.35,0:10:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Whom could it be from?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.03,0:10:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Dealing with kids her age is often a demanding task. \NNo wonder you can't manage it, being the only parent. {to be beyond one's capacities; to be beyond one's powers; to be beyond one's control; to be unmanageable}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.71,0:10:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.22,0:10:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What you said may be true, \Nbut not for our family, that's for certain. {unsure what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.22,0:10:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.86,0:10:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What had happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.26,0:11:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry for startling you. \NA kitten just jumped out in front of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.84,0:11:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Collier - 65 points. \NYou could try just a little better. {really hope it Collier tho doesn't really matter}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.44,0:11:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Scudelli - 80 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.12,0:11:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.42,0:11:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The test was a little more difficult than usual this time, \Nbut you did well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.56,0:11:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte - 92 points! \NA great job, however you look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.40,0:11:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not Lotte, but a completely different person, \Nand yet, I managed it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.16,0:11:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie - 3 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.27,0:11:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The honest score would be 0, but you wrote your name \Nin your most neat handwriting ever, so 3 points it is. {careful; close; thorough; conscientious}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.47,0:11:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.03,0:11:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie, this problem is getting worse \Nwith every semester passing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.68,0:11:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Please ask your father \Nto come to school tomorrow, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.31,0:11:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.25,0:11:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.06,0:11:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does she only asks Annie's dad to come? {/is a father and child family, isn't she}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.55,0:11:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, because she doesn't have a mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.65,0:11:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? Oh, right, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.07,0:12:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.43,0:12:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, welcome, Frau Körner!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.51,0:12:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a day off?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.91,0:12:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I work in the evening today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.27,0:12:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I have half a pound of ham? {leg (meat); round; ham}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.32,0:12:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. By the way, is Fraulein Lotte's burn healing up nicely?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.21,0:12:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Burn?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.11,0:12:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The burn that is on her foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.05,0:12:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? {\i1}My{\i0} Lotte's foot?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.27,0:12:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, she didn't tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.48,0:12:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh well, that was to be expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.12,0:12:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't want to give you an extra worry, \Nso she kept it to herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.59,0:12:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the kind of kid our Lotte is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.11,0:12:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Frau Körner!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.08,0:12:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? Good afternoon, Frau Wagenthaler.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.35,0:12:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Something distressing on your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.03,0:12:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No, nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.74,0:12:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, has Lotte's finger cut \Nhealed up already?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.72,0:12:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Her finger cut... You know about it, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.77,0:13:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I not know it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.26,0:13:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,While I was teaching her to cook, \Nshe cut it like five times in a row, with a kitchen knife!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.86,0:13:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,With a kitchen knife?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.83,0:13:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Just squeezed it with a door, a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.14,0:13:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon, Frau Körner.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.78,0:13:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, glad to see you're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.67,0:13:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Had a lot of work assigned to you lately, hadn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.33,0:13:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.98,0:13:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, well I can't help noticing \Nyou work until late every night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.45,0:13:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The other night, your lights weren't out until the sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.02,0:13:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Until sunrise?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.38,0:13:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, remember the night when it was raining?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.81,0:13:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Night when it was raining?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.96,0:13:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it was raining, \NI couldn't get any sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.52,0:13:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,so I looked out of the window \Nand saw your living room still lit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.13,0:13:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Erm, pretty sure it was \Nwell past three on the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.90,0:13:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.25,0:13:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about Lotte again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.12,0:14:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,She goes to such extremes just to hide it from you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.28,0:14:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be because I keep telling her, \N"You are my little housekeeper, my most precious little Lotte." {completely clueless what she means: I hear I'm a little housewife, I'm so proud of my Lotte," she said.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.74,0:14:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So her determination stems \Nfrom her unwillingness to disappoint you? {again, unsure: so as to meet your expectations, stubbornness; obstinacy; willpower; pride}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.25,0:14:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It all started when she returned from a summer camp. \NSince then, Lotte has been the least Lotte-like.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.98,0:14:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was sort of glad \Nwhen she started to return to norm. {again unsure: I said I don't mind it this way}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.56,0:14:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, because you treasured her so much before, \Nshe now treasures you back just as much? {still fucking unsure: you thought you're being cautious, but cautiousness was reversed}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.93,0:14:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking, in this age \Nkids undergo some major changes, so... {/because her heart is fickle/trembles violently}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.57,0:14:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. This must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.64,0:14:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What must?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.50,0:14:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not unusual that a growing child with only one parent \Nbecomes emotionally fickle as a result of those changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.41,0:14:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-Chief, our world knows countless examples \Nof single parents rearing their children without any problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.02,0:14:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I just wanted to say... You can't argue the fact \Nthat the child's growth tends to be more stable in full families. {/accept calmly that ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.38,0:14:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither can you debate the fact \Nmany single parents rear their kids without any issue. {/is also reality}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.14,0:14:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to excuse me for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.91,0:14:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.87,0:15:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I swear. Why does it come to this, \Nevery single time with Körner?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.18,0:15:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, I can do this myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.23,0:15:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine. Whenever you're doing something now, \NI want a part in that too, however small. {as (much) as possible; as (much) as one can; wherever practicable; if possible​}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.15,0:15:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I can cook myself sometimes, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.45,0:15:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What's gotten into you, mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.15,0:15:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Just have a rest, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.10,0:15:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But you've also got a work to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.73,0:15:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I went home without taking any extra work today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.04,0:15:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they got anything to say about that, \NI'll go find another work.{/move/transfer to another company}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.04,0:15:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! Cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.58,0:15:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, ever since you've been so small, day after day\NI was counting on you to cook dinner for us both.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.86,0:15:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's finally my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.32,0:15:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. She did this every day for mom, \Never since she was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.12,0:15:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And I, ever since I was little, \Nhas been counting on Resi to cook for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.99,0:15:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like Lotte has been cooking for mom. {unsure: lotte is mom's home cooking}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.83,0:15:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, you still remember it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.70,0:15:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.02,0:15:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When you were about three years old, \Nyou were trying to help me with everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.11,0:15:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.90,0:16:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! If nothing else is left to do, \Nyou were helping me place the bowls on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.43,0:16:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Or helped me to pour the soup! {unsure, maybe she means "you were spilling out soup while carrying the bowls}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.06,0:16:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Even while you were still a baby, \Nhelping others was your prime passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.06,0:16:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.67,0:16:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I am not Lotte! \NAnd I will never be Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.94,0:16:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, looks yummy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.20,0:16:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the meal!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.79,0:16:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.57,0:16:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Great to know!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.17,0:16:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Um! I think, I went a bit overboard with salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.61,0:16:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all! \NDelicious, however you look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.47,0:16:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.70,0:16:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.68,0:16:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Mom's home cooking today, compared to everything \N I had ever tried before, is like heaven and earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.54,0:16:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.05,0:16:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, are you making \Nany good progress with school? {to make (good) progress; to move right ahead (with the work); to advance​}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.71,0:16:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.49,0:16:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The test results returned today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.62,0:16:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I got 92 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.05,0:16:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Dandy! Keep that up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.61,0:16:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But say, mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.05,0:16:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.87,0:17:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know that Annie doesn't have a mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.82,0:17:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think I heard about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.82,0:17:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.17,0:17:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie would never have a chance \Nto try her mother's cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.48,0:17:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Homework done and dusted. \NNow, time to go to bed. {actually just "preparations"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.48,0:17:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.73,0:17:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where could she be going at such hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.38,0:17:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.61,0:18:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all? She wanted to ride a swing seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.93,0:18:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Crying...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.49,0:18:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.50,0:18:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.83,0:18:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. You'll also never be able \Nto try mom's cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.07,0:18:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.14,0:18:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.98,0:18:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,forget about me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.28,0:19:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.08,0:19:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're... well and happy, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.12,0:19:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.69,0:19:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.43,0:19:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well and happy! {/this much genki}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.30,0:19:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I also got to try mom's cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.98,0:19:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll be having it afterwards, too! \NYou shouldn't worry about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.74,0:19:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise... Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.34,0:19:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, Luise is right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.98,0:19:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.69,0:19:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise was barely managing to control her urge to emerge \Nfrom her hideout and give her mom the most loving hug ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.49,0:19:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Unable to drop the mask and come clean, \NLuise could almost feel her little heart breaking apart. {to burst (open); to break; to split}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.60,0:20:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"However, come what may, \NI shall keep my solemn promise to Lotte" -
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.67,0:20:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,were Luise's thoughts at this time of doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.16,0:21:30.60,Sign,,0,0,0,,In the next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.90,0:21:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We have switched places!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.14,0:21:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I just met a very talented street artist!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.13,0:21:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm jealous. \NLotte, what kind of boy is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.24,0:21:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He performs under the name of Hans of the Winds, \Nplaying accordion. {guess what is kaze no, would hope ut's this, he not in the book}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.51,0:21:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But he can play piano, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.91,0:21:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? You mean to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.24,0:21:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! Say what you want, \Nbut I want to learn piano, too!
